          <GermlineClassification>Pathogenic</GermlineClassification>
          <Comment Type="public">This sequence change deletes 1 nucleotide in exon 4 of the CLCN1 mRNA (c.469delC), causing a frameshift at codon 157. This creates a premature translational stop signal (p.Leu157Phefs*13) and is expected to result in an absent or disrupted protein product. While this particular variant has not been reported in the literature, loss-of-function variants in CLCN1 are known to cause autosomal recessive forms of myotonia congenita (PMID: 17932099, 22094069, 23739125). For these reasons, this variant has been classified as Pathogenic.</Comment>
